Our community mourns the passing of former Sumter County Sheriff William “Bill Farmer. Sheriff Farmer was a true servant leader, whose life is marked by extraordinary dedication to public service.

For nearly five decades, Sheriff Farmer dedicated his life to law enforcement. Beginning as a patrolman and later serving as a criminal investigator, Chief Deputy, and ultimately as Sumter County Sheriff. Over seven terms and 28 years, he led with integrity, faith, and an unwavering commitment to public service.

It is impossible to fully measure the impact that Sheriff Farmer leaves on Sumter County and the state of Florida. Sandy and I extend our prayers to his family, friends and loved ones as we honor his life and enduring legacy of service.

Today marks the 24th anniversary of 9/11, a day that we will never forget. We will never forget the nearly 3,000 innocent people who perished in the collapse of the World Trade Center Towers, in the fires at the Pentagon and in the crash site of Shanksville, Pennsylvania.

Though America had been brought to a terrifying standstill, she had not been defeated. We found scores of heroes. Heroes like the passengers on United Airlines Flight 93, like the policemen, firefighters, and first responders who sacrificed their lives to save their neighbors. Out of the darkness and rubble of that horrible day arose a national resolve and a united nation full of patriotism. 

May we honor the memory of the innocent victims by renewing that resolve today. May God bless the victims, their families, may God bless our first responders and servicemembers, and may God bless the United States of America.
